Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: mem-usage-ui
Version: 0.1
Summary: UI for memory usage of processes
Home-page: https://github.com/parikls/mem_usage_ui
Author: Dmytro Smyk
Author-email: porovozls@gmail.com
License: UNKNOWN
Description: Description
        ===========
        
        I'm tired of console measuring of memory usage
        ```bash
        while true; do
        ps -C <ProgramName> -o pid=,%mem=,vsz= >> /tmp/mem.log
        gnuplot /tmp/show_mem.plt
        sleep 1
        done &
        ```
        
        Installation
        ============
        
        `pip install mem_usage_ui`
        
        Usage
        =====
        
        - Run in shell: `dsmyk$ mem_usage_ui`
        - Go to `http://localhost:8080`
        
        
        
